commit.message:
update link to HDBC repository

http://software.complete.org/hdbc generates a broken redirect
to github.com.

remove mention of hdbc-anydbm, it's dead

hdbc-anydbm *seems* to have been replaced with hdbc-missingh,
and the latter hasn't been touched in 13 years.  the repository
description says

  AnyDBM extensions for HDBC [Haskell] (unmaintained)

update links to HDBC drivers

http://software.complete.org has been dead for almost 10 years
and the redirects to github.com are broken.

http://software.complete.org/foo redirects to
https://wiki.github.com/jgoerzen/foo which returns this message:

  We didn't receive a proper request from your browser. Please contact us if the problem persists.

on top of that, the same urls without the `wiki.` part give 404,
presumably because the repos have moved to the hdbc github org.
Bump.
